The paper discusses a traitor tracing scheme to protect copyrighted content against collusion attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the design choices for generating biases and optimizing distribution functions, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents a comparison of estimated lengths of fingerprinting codes, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
